posts.raw_content:
I went to go see Melania at the Palisades mall, 20 miles from NYC. It's a big mall, and the fire alarm went off solely in the theater complex. I waited outside the theater for 10 minutes, with the rest of the mall operating as normal, and then decided to go down to my car in the garage downstairs for a smoke. When I was going back up the elevator, they started to tell everyone to leave the mall, but then they started letting people back into the movie theater. The movie started shortly after (with no ads/trailers-- a small win), but the projector was out of focus, out of alignment, and the lights were on for the first half hour of the movie.

It was a good movie, and I plan to see it again with my mom who expressed interest in seeing it. I may go to a different theater though. There's a rather large part of me that thinks that the fire alarm was no coincidence.
